# Vim_and_the_C_toolchain

# Using Vim and C toolchain

Using Vim and the C toolchain usually means:

1. Edit code with Vim\.
2. Compile with GCC or Clang\.
3. Run & debug the resulting program\.
4. Automate builds with __make__\.

## Creating a file in C, compiling using gcc and clang and running it

__Objective__

Learn how to edit, compile, run, and manage C programs using Vim, GCC/Clang, and Makefiles\.

Install __Vim__ if it is not already installed\.

![A black screen with white text

AI-generated content may be incorrect.](data:image/png;base64,)

__gcc hello\.c \-o hello__ compile the program\.

__&& __ only run the next command if the first one succeeds\.

__\./hello__  run the newly compiled program\.

If you do not want to keep the hello executable at all, you can compile, run, and delete the executable afterwards\. It means the executable is not saved\.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

__Clang__ is a modern, open\-source __C, C\+\+, and Objective\-C compiler__\. It does the same job as __gcc__ \(the GNU Compiler Collection\), that is, turning the C source code into machine code you can run\.
